{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"cyberpunk-spineless-bear","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## What\nThe going-forward compact metrics snapshot: a small JSON record appended per CI run (and readable by the command) persisting point-in-time code-health numbers whose history is otherwise ephemeral — coverage %, complexity distribution, clone count — so their movement accrues.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/metrics/snapshot.py` — new: `write_snapshot(dict)` appends a timestamped record to a committed NDJSON file; `read_snapshots(since,until)` yields in-range records for the registry.\n- `reports/metrics-snapshots.ndjson` — new committed artifact (one snapshot per line), mirroring the existing `reports/*.report.json` precedent.\n- `tests/unit/metrics/test_snapshot.py` — new.\n\n## Approach\nCoverage/complexity/clone are computed at a point in time; their trend needs a stored series, which does not exist today. An append-only NDJSON snapshot (not a new event type) is the lowest-friction durable store and matches the existing `reports/` precedent; the command reads it for trend metrics, and until a snapshot exists a metric reports `unavailable`. Append-only and additive.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit: `write_snapshot` then `read_snapshots` round-trips; a range filter excludes out-of-range records; a malformed line is skipped without raising.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/metrics/test_snapshot.py` passes: a written snapshot is read back within its date range (`assert rec in read_snapshots(since,until)`) and excluded outside it.\n- [ ] a corrupt/truncated NDJSON line is skipped and the reader still returns the valid records — unit test asserts count equals the valid-record count.","id":"3275-b164-2e9b-4e66","parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","priority":2,"tags":["metrics"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Going-forward metrics snapshot writer/reader (NDJSON)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784416760378112001,"uuid":"ce867deb-d110-4120-8bd8-6a076c0883c9"}